omily Key Message: We are called to \\"be changed spiritually\\" during Lent; by looking past the tensions and opposition faced by Jesus, we find the \\"crown of glory\\" and a deeper relationship with our Savior.\\n\\nIf today\'s Mass helped you reflect on your Lenten journey, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue bringing the victory of Jesus over death to our global parish!\\n\\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\\n\\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\\n\\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\\n\\n#CatholicMass #DailyMass #Lent2026 #GospelOfJohn #BookOfWisdom #Discipleship #FaithJourney #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV #FatherDavidOLeary", "publishedAt": "2026-03-20T04:00:23Z", "channelTitle": "The CatholicTV Network", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en-US", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "614", "viewCount": "14286", "commentCount": "147", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "true", "duration": "PT28M48S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "licensedContent": false}}', '2026-03-29 09:18:51', '2026-03-29 09:33:12'),
	(15, 1, 'q3S3L-SDZfg', 'DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/19/26 | The Quiet Strength of St. Joseph: Ordinary Life, Extraordinary Destiny', 'daily-catholic-mass-31926-the-quiet-strength-of-st-joseph-ordinary-life-extraordinary-destiny', 'Welcome! Join The CatholicTV Network for the full Daily Catholic Mass celebration on this Solemnity of Saint Joseph, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary.\n\nIn today’s profound Homily, the celebrant reflects on the hidden greatness of St. Joseph, a man described as "quiet, hardworking, sensible, and compassionate". While Joseph understood himself to be an ordinary man, God had chosen an extraordinary destiny for him as the foster father and protector of the Savior. We are reminded that, like Joseph, we may feel ordinary, but God has called each of us to an "extraordinary destiny"—to welcome the Holy Trinity into the home of our hearts. This Mass is a powerful invitation to provide for and protect the divine life entrusted to us, following the righteous example of the Guardian of the Redeemer.\n\nThe Scriptures highlight the fulfillment of God’s covenant and the obedience of faith:\n-The First Reading (2 Samuel 7:4-16): The Lord speaks to Nathan, promising to raise up an heir for David whose kingdom shall be made firm forever. God declares that He will be a father to this heir, and his throne shall stand firm for all eternity.\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 89): A declaration of divine fidelity: "The Son of David will live forever".\n-The Second Reading (Romans 4:13-22): St. Paul reflects on the righteousness that comes from faith, citing Abraham, who "believed, hoping against hope," as the father of many nations.\n-The Holy Gospel (Matthew 1:16-24): The genealogy of Jesus leads to Joseph, the husband of Mary. Upon learning of Mary’s pregnancy, the righteous Joseph intends to divorce her quietly to save her from shame. However, an angel appears to him in a dream, revealing the child is conceived through the Holy Spirit and shall be named Jesus, for "he will save his people from their sins". Joseph awakes and immediately does as the Lord commanded.\n\nMay the Lord "defend with unfailing protection" the family He has nourished at His altar as we rejoice in this great solemnity.\n\nMass Chapters for Navigation\n\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 0:57\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:33\n-First Reading: 3:08\n-Responsorial Psalm: 3:46\n-Second Reading: 5:21\n-Gospel: 7:11\n-Homily: 8:49\n-The Creed: 12:08\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 12:49\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 13:47\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 15:55\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:16\n-Communion: 25:39\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:04\n\nTheological & Liturgical Context\n-Solemnity: St. Joseph, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary, a "just man" given as a wise and faithful servant to watch over the household of God.\n-Gospel Focus: The Obedience of Faith; Joseph demonstrates that holiness often consists in quiet, prompt obedience to God’s will, even when that will disrupts our own plans, making him a model for all who seek to provide a "home" for Christ in their lives.\n-Homily Key Message: Joseph’s "paradoxical" awakening through a dream reminds us that God often speaks in the stillness of our lives, inviting us to see past our "ordinary" self-perception to the high calling of divine life within us.\n\nIf today’s Mass helped you appreciate the beauty of St. Joseph’s silent witness, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue sharing the "victory of Jesus over death" with our global parish family!\n\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\n\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\n\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\n\n#StJoseph #CatholicMass #Solemnity #GospelOfMatthew #SaintJoseph #PatronOfTheChurch #FaithfulProtector #OrdinaryHoliness #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q3S3L-SDZfg/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-03-19 03:00:55', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q3S3L-SDZfg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/q3S3L-SDZfg', 'PT28M48S', 15835, 0, 14, '{"id": "q3S3L-SDZfg", "etag": "9omFRZ812xYQcfyn6Nl73qzCtEw", "kind": "youtube#video", "snippet": {"tags": ["daily Mass", "Catholic", "tv mass", "streaming mass", "roman catholic", "youtube mass", "archdiocese of boston mass", "todays mass", "online liturgy", "Thursday Mass", "Father Tom Macdonald"], "title": "DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/19/26 | The Quiet Strength of St. Joseph: Ordinary Life, Extraordinary Destiny", "channelId": "UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ", "localized": {"title": "DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/19/26 | The Quiet Strength of St. Joseph: Ordinary Life, Extraordinary Destiny", "description": "Welcome! Join The CatholicTV Network for the full Daily Catholic Mass celebration on this Solemnity of Saint Joseph, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary.\\n\\nIn today’s profound Homily, the celebrant reflects on the hidden greatness of St. Joseph, a man described as \\"quiet, hardworking, sensible, and compassionate\\". While Joseph understood himself to be an ordinary man, God had chosen an extraordinary destiny for him as the foster father and protector of the Savior. We are reminded that, like Joseph, we may feel ordinary, but God has called each of us to an \\"extraordinary destiny\\"—to welcome the Holy Trinity into the home of our hearts. This Mass is a powerful invitation to provide for and protect the divine life entrusted to us, following the righteous example of the Guardian of the Redeemer.\\n\\nThe Scriptures highlight the fulfillment of God’s covenant and the obedience of faith:\\n-The First Reading (2 Samuel 7:4-16): The Lord speaks to Nathan, promising to raise up an heir for David whose kingdom shall be made firm forever. God declares that He will be a father to this heir, and his throne shall stand firm for all eternity.\\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 89): A declaration of divine fidelity: \\"The Son of David will live forever\\".\\n-The Second Reading (Romans 4:13-22): St. Paul reflects on the righteousness that comes from faith, citing Abraham, who \\"believed, hoping against hope,\\" as the father of many nations.\\n-The Holy Gospel (Matthew 1:16-24): The genealogy of Jesus leads to Joseph, the husband of Mary. Upon learning of Mary’s pregnancy, the righteous Joseph intends to divorce her quietly to save her from shame. However, an angel appears to him in a dream, revealing the child is conceived through the Holy Spirit and shall be named Jesus, for \\"he will save his people from their sins\\". Joseph awakes and immediately does as the Lord commanded.\\n\\nMay the Lord \\"defend with unfailing protection\\" the family He has nourished at His altar as we rejoice in this great solemnity.\\n\\nMass Chapters for Navigation\\n\\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 0:57\\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:33\\n-First Reading: 3:08\\n-Responsorial Psalm: 3:46\\n-Second Reading: 5:21\\n-Gospel: 7:11\\n-Homily: 8:49\\n-The Creed: 12:08\\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 12:49\\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 13:47\\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 15:55\\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:16\\n-Communion: 25:39\\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:04\\n\\nTheological & Liturgical Context\\n-Solemnity: St. Joseph, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary, a \\"just man\\" given as a wise and faithful servant to watch over the household of God.\\n-Gospel Focus: The Obedience of Faith; Joseph demonstrates that holiness often consists in quiet, prompt obedience to God’s will, even when that will disrupts our own plans, making him a model for all who seek to provide a \\"home\\" for Christ in their lives.\\n-Homily Key Message: Joseph’s \\"paradoxical\\" awakening through a dream reminds us that God often speaks in the stillness of our lives, inviting us to see past our \\"ordinary\\" self-perception to the high calling of divine life within us.\\n\\nIf today’s Mass helped you appreciate the beauty of St. Joseph’s silent witness, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue sharing the \\"victory of Jesus over death\\" with our global parish family!\\n\\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\\n\\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\\n\\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\\n\\n#StJoseph #CatholicMass #Solemnity #GospelOfMatthew #SaintJoseph #PatronOfTheChurch #FaithfulProtector #OrdinaryHoliness #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV"}, "categoryId": "29", "thumbnails": {"high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q3S3L-SDZfg/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q3S3L-SDZfg/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q3S3L-SDZfg/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q3S3L-SDZfg/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q3S3L-SDZfg/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}}, "description": "Welcome! Join The CatholicTV Network for the full Daily Catholic Mass celebration on this Solemnity of Saint Joseph, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary.\\n\\nIn today’s profound Homily, the celebrant reflects on the hidden greatness of St. Joseph, a man described as \\"quiet, hardworking, sensible, and compassionate\\". While Joseph understood himself to be an ordinary man, God had chosen an extraordinary destiny for him as the foster father and protector of the Savior. We are reminded that, like Joseph, we may feel ordinary, but God has called each of us to an \\"extraordinary destiny\\"—to welcome the Holy Trinity into the home of our hearts. This Mass is a powerful invitation to provide for and protect the divine life entrusted to us, following the righteous example of the Guardian of the Redeemer.\\n\\nThe Scriptures highlight the fulfillment of God’s covenant and the obedience of faith:\\n-The First Reading (2 Samuel 7:4-16): The Lord speaks to Nathan, promising to raise up an heir for David whose kingdom shall be made firm forever. God declares that He will be a father to this heir, and his throne shall stand firm for all eternity.\\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 89): A declaration of divine fidelity: \\"The Son of David will live forever\\".\\n-The Second Reading (Romans 4:13-22): St. Paul reflects on the righteousness that comes from faith, citing Abraham, who \\"believed, hoping against hope,\\" as the father of many nations.\\n-The Holy Gospel (Matthew 1:16-24): The genealogy of Jesus leads to Joseph, the husband of Mary. Upon learning of Mary’s pregnancy, the righteous Joseph intends to divorce her quietly to save her from shame. However, an angel appears to him in a dream, revealing the child is conceived through the Holy Spirit and shall be named Jesus, for \\"he will save his people from their sins\\". Joseph awakes and immediately does as the Lord commanded.\\n\\nMay the Lord \\"defend with unfailing protection\\" the family He has nourished at His altar as we rejoice in this great solemnity.\\n\\nMass Chapters for Navigation\\n\\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 0:57\\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:33\\n-First Reading: 3:08\\n-Responsorial Psalm: 3:46\\n-Second Reading: 5:21\\n-Gospel: 7:11\\n-Homily: 8:49\\n-The Creed: 12:08\\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 12:49\\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 13:47\\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 15:55\\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:16\\n-Communion: 25:39\\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:04\\n\\nTheological & Liturgical Context\\n-Solemnity: St. Joseph, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary, a \\"just man\\" given as a wise and faithful servant to watch over the household of God.\\n-Gospel Focus: The Obedience of Faith; Joseph demonstrates that holiness often consists in quiet, prompt obedience to God’s will, even when that will disrupts our own plans, making him a model for all who seek to provide a \\"home\\" for Christ in their lives.\\n-Homily Key Message: Joseph’s \\"paradoxical\\" awakening through a dream reminds us that God often speaks in the stillness of our lives, inviting us to see past our \\"ordinary\\" self-perception to the high calling of divine life within us.\\n\\nIf today’s Mass helped you appreciate the beauty of St. Joseph’s silent witness, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue sharing the \\"victory of Jesus over death\\" with our global parish family!\\n\\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\\n\\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\\n\\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\\n\\n#StJoseph #CatholicMass #Solemnity #GospelOfMatthew #SaintJoseph #PatronOfTheChurch #FaithfulProtector #OrdinaryHoliness #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV", "publishedAt": "2026-03-19T04:00:55Z", "channelTitle": "The CatholicTV Network", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en-US", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "727", "viewCount": "15835", "commentCount": "129", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "true", "duration": "PT28M48S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "licensedContent": false}}', '2026-03-29 09:18:51', '2026-03-29 09:33:12'),
	(16, 1, '9x2iLtYPKuY', 'DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/18/26 | Divine Fidelity and the Promise of Restoration', 'daily-catholic-mass-31826-divine-fidelity-and-the-promise-of-restoration', 'Welcome! Join The CatholicTV Network for the full Daily Catholic Mass celebration on this Wednesday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\n\nIn today’s reverent Homily, Father Dan O\'Connell reflects on the "great importance of allowing our God to be primary" in our lives. Drawing from the comforting words of the Prophet Isaiah and the profound discourse of Jesus in the Gospel of John, Father Dan explores the mystery of divine fidelity. He reminds us that even if a mother could forget her infant, God will never forget us, and His Son is ever by our side, offering the gifts that come only from the Father. This Mass is a powerful invitation to move through our Lenten journey with the confidence that we are "schooled by Lenten prayer" and nourished by the "heavenly remedy" of the Eucharist.\n\nThe Scriptures highlight the enduring love of the Father and the authority of the Son:\n-The First Reading (Isaiah 49:8-15): The Lord speaks of a "time of favor" and a "day of salvation," promising to restore the land and comfort His people. He reassures those who feel abandoned, declaring that He has carved them on the palms of His hands and will never forget them: "Can a mother forget her infant... even should she forget, I will never forget you".\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 145): A proclamation of God\'s goodness: "The Lord is kind and merciful".\n-The Holy Gospel (John 5:17-30): Jesus responds to those who question His work on the Sabbath by revealing His intimate union with the Father: "The Son cannot do anything on his own, but only what he sees the Father doing". He proclaims that the Father has given the Son the power to give life to whom He wills and has entrusted all judgment to Him, so that all may honor the Son as they honor the Father.\n\nMay the heavenly gifts we receive today bring us the protection and grace we need to walk in God\'s ways and give glory to Him by our lives.\n\nMass Chapters for Navigation\n\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 0:57\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:35\n-First Reading: 3:26\n-Responsorial Psalm: 5:08\n-Gospel: 7:30\n-Homily: 10:24\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 16:18\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 17:34\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 19:13\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:21\n-Communion: 25:06\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:08\n\nTheological & Liturgical Context\n-Season: Wednesday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\n-Gospel Focus: The Divine Sonship and Authority; Jesus reveals that His mission is not a departure from the Father’s will but its perfect fulfillment, emphasizing that to hear His Word and believe in the One who sent Him is to possess eternal life.\n-Homily Key Message: We are encouraged to "allow our God to be primary," trusting that the "victory of Jesus over death" is won through this perfect obedience to the Father, which we are invited to mirror during this holy season.\n\nIf today\'s Mass helped you feel the presence of the Lord by your side, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue bringing this great prayer to our global parish family!\n\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\n\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\n\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\n\n#CatholicMass #DailyMass #Lent2026 #GospelOfJohn #ProphetIsaiah #DivineFidelity #EternalLife #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV #FatherDanOConnell', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9x2iLtYPKuY/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-03-18 03:00:11', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9x2iLtYPKuY', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/9x2iLtYPKuY', 'PT28M48S', 15618, 0, 15, '{"id": "9x2iLtYPKuY", "etag": "JJtWY5Mh_etz3k_G24sXBpCqgB8", "kind": "youtube#video", "snippet": {"tags": ["daily Mass", "Catholic", "tv mass", "streaming mass", "roman catholic", "youtube mass", "archdiocese of boston mass", "todays mass", "online liturgy", "Wednesday Mass", "Father Dan O\'Connell"], "title": "DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/18/26 | Divine Fidelity and the Promise of Restoration", "channelId": "UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ", "localized": {"title": "DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/18/26 | Divine Fidelity and the Promise of Restoration", "description": "Welcome! Join The CatholicTV Network for the full Daily Catholic Mass celebration on this Wednesday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\\n\\nIn today’s reverent Homily, Father Dan O\'Connell reflects on the \\"great importance of allowing our God to be primary\\" in our lives. Drawing from the comforting words of the Prophet Isaiah and the profound discourse of Jesus in the Gospel of John, Father Dan explores the mystery of divine fidelity. He reminds us that even if a mother could forget her infant, God will never forget us, and His Son is ever by our side, offering the gifts that come only from the Father. This Mass is a powerful invitation to move through our Lenten journey with the confidence that we are \\"schooled by Lenten prayer\\" and nourished by the \\"heavenly remedy\\" of the Eucharist.\\n\\nThe Scriptures highlight the enduring love of the Father and the authority of the Son:\\n-The First Reading (Isaiah 49:8-15): The Lord speaks of a \\"time of favor\\" and a \\"day of salvation,\\" promising to restore the land and comfort His people. He reassures those who feel abandoned, declaring that He has carved them on the palms of His hands and will never forget them: \\"Can a mother forget her infant... even should she forget, I will never forget you\\".\\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 145): A proclam