): The Lord speaks of a \\"time of favor\\" and a \\"day of salvation,\\" promising to restore the land and comfort His people. He reassures those who feel abandoned, declaring that He has carved them on the palms of His hands and will never forget them: \\"Can a mother forget her infant... even should she forget, I will never forget you\\".\\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 145): A proclamation of God\'s goodness: \\"The Lord is kind and merciful\\".\\n-The Holy Gospel (John 5:17-30): Jesus responds to those who question His work on the Sabbath by revealing His intimate union with the Father: \\"The Son cannot do anything on his own, but only what he sees the Father doing\\". He proclaims that the Father has given the Son the power to give life to whom He wills and has entrusted all judgment to Him, so that all may honor the Son as they honor the Father.\\n\\nMay the heavenly gifts we receive today bring us the protection and grace we need to walk in God\'s ways and give glory to Him by our lives.\\n\\nMass Chapters for Navigation\\n\\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 0:57\\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:35\\n-First Reading: 3:26\\n-Responsorial Psalm: 5:08\\n-Gospel: 7:30\\n-Homily: 10:24\\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 16:18\\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 17:34\\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 19:13\\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:21\\n-Communion: 25:06\\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:08\\n\\nTheological & Liturgical Context\\n-Season: Wednesday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\\n-Gospel Focus: The Divine Sonship and Authority; Jesus reveals that His mission is not a departure from the Father’s will but its perfect fulfillment, emphasizing that to hear His Word and believe in the One who sent Him is to possess eternal life.\\n-Homily Key Message: We are encouraged to \\"allow our God to be primary,\\" trusting that the \\"victory of Jesus over death\\" is won through this perfect obedience to the Father, which we are invited to mirror during this holy season.\\n\\nIf today\'s Mass helped you feel the presence of the Lord by your side, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue bringing this great prayer to our global parish family!\\n\\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\\n\\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\\n\\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\\n\\n#CatholicMass #DailyMass #Lent2026 #GospelOfJohn #ProphetIsaiah #DivineFidelity #EternalLife #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV #FatherDanOConnell", "publishedAt": "2026-03-18T04:00:11Z", "channelTitle": "The CatholicTV Network", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en-US", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "698", "viewCount": "15618", "commentCount": "113", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "true", "duration": "PT28M48S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "licensedContent": false}}', '2026-03-29 09:18:51', '2026-03-29 09:33:12'),
	(17, 1, 'FDa8rP7JMk8', 'ST. PATRICK\'S DAY MASS 3/17/26 | A Pilgrim Way: Faith, Protection, and the Glory of the Father', 'st-patricks-day-mass-31726-a-pilgrim-way-faith-protection-and-the-glory-of-the-father', 'Happy St. Patrick’s Day! Join The CatholicTV Network as we celebrate the Solemnity of St. Patrick, the patron saint of the Archdiocese of Boston.\n\nIn today’s reverent Homily, Monsignor Liam Bergin reflects on the legacy of St. Patrick and the life-giving power of God\'s presence. Drawing from the vision of the Prophet Ezekiel and the healing at the pool of Bethesda, Monsignor Bergin explores how the "river of life" flowing from the Temple brings healing wherever it goes. We are encouraged to see ourselves as pilgrims, guided and protected by the same faith that fueled St. Patrick’s mission to the people of Ireland. This Mass is a beautiful invitation to experience a "foretaste of the heavenly banquet" and to resolve to stay true to God\'s commandments in our daily walk.\n\nMay our communion today, in the company of St. Patrick and all our forebears in faith, strengthen us to be true to the Gospel on earth so we may share eternal joy in Heaven.\n\nMass Chapters for Navigation\n\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 0:58\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:28\n-First Reading: 3:04\n-Responsorial Psalm: 4:00\n-Gospel: 6:34\n-Homily: 7:45\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 14:53\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 16:08\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 17:23\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 22:43\n-Communion: 25:17\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 26:49\n\nTheological & Liturgical Context\n-Feast Day: Solemnity of St. Patrick, Bishop, whose faith brought the light of Christ to Ireland and continues to inspire the pilgrim way of the Church today.\n-Gospel Focus: The Sovereignty of Christ over the Sabbath; Jesus’ act of healing reveals that His mission is to restore humanity to wholeness, showing that the power of God\'s Word can accomplish what human effort cannot.\n-Homily Key Message: We pray for the grace to "guide and protect us on our pilgrim way"; just as the waters of Ezekiel brought life to the desert, we seek the "foretaste of the heavenly banquet" to nourish us as we proclaim the Lord with our lives.\n\nIf today’s celebration of St. Patrick helped you feel closer to God\'s presence, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support and donations help us continue to proclaim the victory of Jesus to our global community of faith!\n\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\n\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\n\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\n\n#StPatricksDay #CatholicMass #ArchdioceseOfBoston #GospelOfJohn #ProphetEzekiel #HealingWaters #FaithfulPilgrims #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV #MonsignorLiamBergen', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FDa8rP7JMk8/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-03-17 03:00:13', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FDa8rP7JMk8', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/FDa8rP7JMk8', 'PT28M48S', 19430, 0, 16, '{"id": "FDa8rP7JMk8", "etag": "Y3IJLS7y_mK5IqaKudXOD7fJJxg", "kind": "youtube#video", "snippet": {"tags": ["daily Mass", "Catholic", "tv mass", "streaming mass", "roman catholic", "youtube mass", "archdiocese of boston mass", "todays mass", "online liturgy", "Tuesday Mass", "Monsignor Liam Bergin"], "title": "ST. PATRICK\'S DAY MASS 3/17/26 | A Pilgrim Way: Faith, Protection, and the Glory of the Father", "channelId": "UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ", "localized": {"title": "ST. PATRICK\'S DAY MASS 3/17/26 | A Pilgrim Way: Faith, Protection, and the Glory of the Father", "description": "Happy St. Patrick’s Day! Join The Cath