s like custom CatholicTV emojis:\\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\\n\\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\\n\\n#StPatricksDay #CatholicMass #ArchdioceseOfBoston #GospelOfJohn #ProphetEzekiel #HealingWaters #FaithfulPilgrims #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV #MonsignorLiamBergen", "publishedAt": "2026-03-17T04:00:13Z", "channelTitle": "The CatholicTV Network", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en-US", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "803", "viewCount": "19430", "commentCount": "151", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "true", "duration": "PT28M48S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "licensedContent": false}}', '2026-03-29 09:18:51', '2026-03-29 09:33:12'),
	(18, 1, '4mRyzMsIYAg', 'DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/16/26 | The Power of God’s Word and the Official’s Faith', 'daily-catholic-mass-31626-the-power-of-gods-word-and-the-officials-faith', 'Welcome! Join The CatholicTV Network for the full Daily Catholic Mass celebration on this Monday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\n\nIn today’s reverent Homily, Father Chris Bae reflects on the "mysteries beyond all telling" through which God renews the world. Drawing from the promise of the Prophet Isaiah and the healing of the royal official\'s son, Father Bae explores how God\'s Word brings life by making us new. We are encouraged to trust in the Lord’s mercy, especially in times of affliction, and to allow the "holy gifts" of the Eucharist to lead us toward things eternal. This Mass is a powerful invitation to move beyond the search for "signs and wonders" and to simply believe in the Word that Jesus speaks to us today.\n\nThe Scriptures highlight the joy of God’s new creation and the efficacy of Christ’s command:\n-The First Reading (Isaiah 65:17-21): The Lord announces the creation of "new heavens and a new earth," where the past shall not be remembered. He commands His people to rejoice forever in what He creates, promising a Jerusalem that is a joy and a people that are a delight, where the sound of weeping shall be heard no more.\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 30): A song of thanksgiving for deliverance: "I will praise you, Lord, for you have rescued me".\n-The Holy Gospel (John 4:43-54): Jesus returns to Cana in Galilee, where a royal official begs Him to heal his son who is near death. Jesus tells him, "You may go; your son will live," and the man believes the Word spoken to him. Upon discovering the boy was healed at the exact moment Jesus spoke, the official and his whole household come to believe.\n\nMay we always ponder what is worthy and love the Lord in all sincerity as we are sanctified through these sacred mysteries.\n\nMass Chapters for Navigation\n\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 1:00\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:19\n-First Reading: 2:50\n-Responsorial Psalm: 3:53\n-Gospel: 6:34\n-Homily: 8:35\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 13:11\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 14:13\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 16:27\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:18\n-Communion: 26:00\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:24\n\nTheological & Liturgical Context\n-Season: Monday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\n-Gospel Focus: The Power of the Word; Jesus demonstrates that His authority transcends physical distance, revealing that faith is perfected when we trust in His promise even before we see the result.\n-Homily Key Message: We pray for the Church to be renewed through "mysteries beyond all telling"; by acknowledging our sins and affliction, we open ourselves to the "holy gifts" that sanctify us and lead us to eternal life.\n\nIf today\'s Mass helped you rejoice in God\'s mercy, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue bringing the victory of Jesus over death to our global parish family!\n\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\n\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\n\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\n\n#CatholicMass #DailyMass #Lent2026 #GospelOfJohn #ProphetIsaiah #HealingMiracle #NewCreation #Faith #Catholic #Theology #VirtualMass #CatholicTV #FatherChrisBae', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4mRyzMsIYAg/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-03-16 03:00:04', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4mRyzMsIYAg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/4mRyzMsIYAg', 'PT28M48S', 15131, 0, 17, '{"id": "4mRyzMsIYAg", "etag": "fE507MoLR3Tof88MwqK00zBZFe4", "kind": "youtube#video", "snippet": {"tags": ["daily Mass", "Catholic", "tv mass", "streaming mass", "roman catholic", "youtube mass", "archdiocese of boston mass", "todays mass", "online liturgy", "Monday Mass", "Father Christopher Bae"], "title": "DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/16/26 | The Power of God’s Word and the Official’s Faith", "channelId": "UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ", "localized": {"title": "DAILY CATHOLIC MASS 3/16/26 | The Power of God’s Word and the Official’s Faith", "description": "Welcome! Join The CatholicTV Network for the full Daily Catholic Mass celebration on this Monday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\\n\\nIn today’s reverent Homily, Father Chris Bae reflects on the \\"mysteries beyond all telling\\" through which God renews the world. Drawing from the promise of the Prophet Isaiah and the healing of the royal official\'s son, Father Bae explores how God\'s Word brings life by making us new. We are encouraged to trust in the Lord’s mercy, especially in times of affliction, and to allow the \\"holy gifts\\" of the Eucharist to lead us toward things eternal. This Mass is a powerful invitation to move beyond the search for \\"signs and wonders\\" and to simply believe in the Word that Jesus speaks to us today.\\n\\nThe Scriptures highlight the joy of God’s new creation and the efficacy of Christ’s command:\\n-The First Reading (Isaiah 65:17-21): The Lord announces the creation of \\"new heavens and a new earth,\\" where the past shall not be remembered. He commands His people to rejoice forever in what He creates, promising a Jerusalem that is a joy and a people that are a delight, where the sound of weeping shall be heard no more.\\n-The Responsorial Psalm (Ps 30): A song of thanksgiving for deliverance: \\"I will praise you, Lord, for you have rescued me\\".\\n-The Holy Gospel (John 4:43-54): Jesus returns to Cana in Galilee, where a royal official begs Him to heal his son who is near death. Jesus tells him, \\"You may go; your son will live,\\" and the man believes the Word spoken to him. Upon discovering the boy was healed at the exact moment Jesus spoke, the official and his whole household come to believe.\\n\\nMay we always ponder what is worthy and love the Lord in all sincerity as we are sanctified through these sacred mysteries.\\n\\nMass Chapters for Navigation\\n\\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 1:00\\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:19\\n-First Reading: 2:50\\n-Responsorial Psalm: 3:53\\n-Gospel: 6:34\\n-Homily: 8:35\\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 13:11\\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 14:13\\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 16:27\\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:18\\n-Communion: 26:00\\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:24\\n\\nTheological & Liturgical Context\\n-Season: Monday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\\n-Gospel Focus: The Power of the Word; Jesus demonstrates that His authority transcends physical distance, revealing that faith is perfected when we trust in His promise even before we see the result.\\n-Homily Key Message: We pray for the Church to be renewed through \\"mysteries beyond all telling\\"; by acknowledging our sins and affliction, we open ourselves to the \\"holy gifts\\" that sanctify us and lead us to eternal life.\\n\\nIf today\'s Mass helped you rejoice in God\'s mercy, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue bringing the victory of Jesus over death to our global parish family!\\n\\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\\n\\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\\n\\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\\nLike us on Facebook: http://bit.ly/2LWw1tm\\nFollow us on Twitter: http://bit.ly/31eG1lf\\nFollow us on Instagram: http://bit.ly/339rEAf\\n\\n#CatholicMass #DailyMass #Lent2026 #GospelOfJohn #Prophe