: Jesus returns to Cana in Galilee, where a royal official begs Him to heal his son who is near death. Jesus tells him, \\"You may go; your son will live,\\" and the man believes the Word spoken to him. Upon discovering the boy was healed at the exact moment Jesus spoke, the official and his whole household come to believe.\\n\\nMay we always ponder what is worthy and love the Lord in all sincerity as we are sanctified through these sacred mysteries.\\n\\nMass Chapters for Navigation\\n\\n-Introductory Rites / Penitential Act: 1:00\\n-Collect (Opening Prayer): 2:19\\n-First Reading: 2:50\\n-Responsorial Psalm: 3:53\\n-Gospel: 6:34\\n-Homily: 8:35\\n-Prayers Of The Faithful: 13:11\\n-Liturgy of the Eucharist Begins: 14:13\\n-Eucharistic Prayer / Consecration: 16:27\\n-The Lord\'s Prayer: 23:18\\n-Communion: 26:00\\n-Concluding Rites / Final Blessing: 27:24\\n\\nTheological & Liturgical Context\\n-Season: Monday of the Fourth Week of Lent.\\n-Gospel Focus: The Power of the Word; Jesus demonstrates that His authority transcends physical distance, revealing that faith is perfected when we trust in His promise even before we see the result.\\n-Homily Key Message: We pray for the Church to be renewed through \\"mysteries beyond all telling\\"; by acknowledging our sins and affliction, we open ourselves to the \\"holy gifts\\" that sanctify us and lead us to eternal life.\\n\\nIf today\'s Mass helped you rejoice in God\'s mercy, please Like this video and Subscribe to The CatholicTV Network. Your support allows us to continue bringing the victory of Jesus over death to our global parish family!\\n\\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel so you never miss a daily Mass: http://bit.ly/31Ceiuu\\n\\nJoin this channel to get access to perks like custom CatholicTV emojis:\\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCORAZZmab8apqy2TMHZlZVQ/join\\n\\nDonate to CatholicTV and join us in our mission: https://www.catholictv.org/donate\\nCatholicTV website: http://bit.ly/2KlLFuX\\nLike us on Faceboo