	(67, 3, 'uP_bypBlS1c', 'How to Respond to the Claim Jesus Was Just a Wise Teacher? AMA Jesus w/ Tom Nash', 'how-to-respond-to-the-claim-jesus-was-just-a-wise-teacher-ama-jesus-w-tom-nash', 'More Catholic Answers: https://www.catholic.com\nDonate: https://www.catholicanswersradio.com\nBook a speaker: https://www.catholic.com/speakers\n\nSUBSCRIBE TO CA LIVE CLUB:\nhttps://www.catholic.com/radioclub?email\n\nTopic: AMA: Jesus\nGuest: Tom Nash\n\n0:00 Intro\n01:45 - How do we respond to the Claim Jesus was Just a Wise Teacher?  \n10:56 - I’m new to the faith, getting baptized soon, and I’m going back into the Army. I’ve seen a lot of heretical things in parishes. As I move to a new station, how do I navigate making sure I’m in a parish and diocese that is in communion with Rome?  \n18:56 - When did Catholic priests start using vestments?  \n22:07 - I am dogsitting for a family member who is out of town, and they have tarot cards in the house. What should I do with them?  \n30:49 - In John 20:17 Jesus calls God “my God and your God.” Is Jesus worshipping the Father because of the hypostatic union? Would that have also been the case before the Incarnation? Does the Holy Spirit worship the Father?  \n36:49 - If Jesus would be born today, would he still have died for our sins, considering how bad things are?  \n43:58 - When Moses wrote the creation story, what were his sources -- where did he get it from?  \n48:40 - I am in OCIA. I am feeling spiritual attacks and temptation to backslide. Are these attacks to be expected as I enter the final weeks before entering the Church?  \n50:57 - What are good books to read or something to listen to learn about the faith? I watch you guys and Joe Heschmeyer. I want to dive into some more source material, like the stuff you guys draw from.  \n53:20 - Why is Joseph not mentioned much in the Bible?  \n\nFor more, visit catholic.com', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uP_bypBlS1c/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-03-16 23:26:46', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uP_bypBlS1c', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/uP_bypBlS1c', 'PT55M5S', 922, 0, 18, '{"id": "uP_bypBlS1c", "etag": "k9R2Zsg_BIaZ1xgp83jAlF8c0Gk", "kind": "youtube#video", "snippet": {"title": "How to Respond to the Claim Jesus Was Just a Wise Teacher? AMA Jesus w/ Tom Nash", "channelId": "UCvwbLBTkuIwqNm9kHUqWRnw", "localized": {"title": "How to Respond to the Claim Jesus Was Just a Wise Teacher? AMA Jesus w/ Tom Nash", "description": "More Catholic Answers: https://www.catholic.com\\nDonate: https://www.catholicanswersradio.com\\nBook a speaker: https://www.catholic.com/speakers\\n\\nSUBSCRIBE TO CA LIVE CLUB:\\nhttps://www.catholic.com/radioclub?email\\n\\nTopic: AMA: Jesus\\nGuest: Tom Nash\\n\\n0:00 Intro\\n01:45 - How do we respond to the Claim Jesus was Just a Wise Teacher?  \\n10:56 - I’m new to the faith, getting baptized soon, and I’m going back into the Army. I’ve seen a lot of heretical things in parishes. As I move to a new station, how do I navigate making sure I’m in a parish and diocese that is in communion with Rome?  \\n18:56 - When did Catholic priests start using vestments?  \\n22:07 - I am dogsitting for a family member who is out of town, and they have tarot cards in the house. What should I do with them?  \\n30:49 - In John 20:17 Jesus calls God “my God and your God.” Is Jesus worshipping the Father because of the hypostatic union? Would that have also been the case before the Incarnation? Does the Holy Spirit worship the Father?  \\n36:49 - If Jesus would be born today, would he still have died for our sins, considering how bad things are?  \\n43:58 - When Moses wrote the creation story, what were his sources -- where did he get it from?  \\n48:40 - I am in OCIA. I am feeling spiritual attacks and temptation to backslide. Are these attacks to be expected as I enter the final weeks before entering the Church?  \\n50:57 - What are good books to read or something to listen to learn about the faith? I watch you guys and Joe Heschmeyer. I want to dive into some more source material, like the stuff you guys draw from.  \\n53:20 - Why is Joseph not mentioned much in the Bible?  \\n\\nFor more, visit catholic.com"}, "categoryId": "24", "thumbnails": {"high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uP_bypBlS1c/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uP_bypBlS1c/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uP_bypBlS1c/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uP_bypBlS1c/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uP_bypBlS1c/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}}, "description": "More Catholic Answers: https://www.catholic.com\\nDonate: https://www.catholicanswersradio.com\\nBook a speaker: https://www.catholic.com/speakers\\n\\nSUBSCRIBE TO CA LIVE CLUB:\\nhttps://www.catholic.com/radioclub?email\\n\\nTopic: AMA: Jesus\\nGuest: Tom Nash\\n\\n0:00 Intro\\n01:45 - How do we respond to the Claim Jesus was Just a Wise Teacher?  \\n10:56 - I’m new to the faith, getting baptized soon, and I’m going back into the Army. I’ve seen a lot of heretical things in parishes. As I move to a new station, how do I navigate making sure I’m in a parish and diocese that is in communion with Rome?  \\n18:56 - When did Catholic priests start using vestments?  \\n22:07 - I am dogsitting for a family member who is out of town, and they have tarot cards in the house. What should I do with them?  \\n30:49 - In John 20:17 Jesus calls God “my God and your God.” Is Jesus worshipping the Father because of the hypostatic union? Would that have also been the case before the Incarnation? Does the Holy Spirit worship the Father?  \\n36:49 - If Jesus would be born today, would he still have died for our sins, considering how bad things are?  \\n43:58 - When Moses wrote the creation story, what were his sources -- where did he get it from?  \\n48:40 - I am in 