.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kRGuGOsjXbU/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kRGuGOsjXbU/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}}, "description": "More Catholic Answers: https://www.catholic.com\\nDonate: https://www.catholicanswersradio.com\\nBook a speaker: https://www.catholic.com/speakers\\n\\nSUBSCRIBE TO CA LIVE CLUB:\\nhttps://www.catholic.com/radioclub?email\\n\\nTopic: Were the Gospels Written Earlier? Eucharist and the Bible\\nGuest: Jimmy Akin\\n\\nDescription:\\n0:00 Intro\\n01:27 - Were the Gospels Written Earlier then We Were Taught?\\n14:44 - Why are pregnant women allowed to receive the Eucharist?\\n22:18 - When did the terms low, high and solemn high Mass develop for the Latin Mass?\\n28:45 - At what point should we take the bible stories more literally?\\n41:00 - Did Jesus descend into the Hell of the just? Is this different from Hell and why did Jesus need to do this?\\n45:36 - Why isn’t the book of Enoch in the Bible?\\n1:03:17 - What factors had the Jews expecting the messiah in the 1st century?\\n1:07:03 - Where is a good start when reading the Deuterocanonical books? Books Protestant bible doesn’t?\\n1:12:29 - Should Isaiah 65:20 be taken literally or symbolically?\\n1:19:30 - How do you decide what content to consume when reading or listening to videos?\\n1:28:42 - Why do people rip or tear garments so often in the Old Testament?\\n1:34:48 - What is the historical tradition behind male altar servers?\\n1:46:22 - What does the church know or teach about the life of St. Joseph?\\n1:50:51 - Could blasphemy of the Holy Spirit prevent Jeffrey Dahmer Baptism from being valid?\\n\\nFor more, visit catholic.com", "publishedAt": "2026-03-14T12:01:24Z", "channelTitle": "Catholic Answers Live", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "144", "viewCount": "2875", "commentCount": "6", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "true", "duration": "PT1H54M32S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "licensedContent": true}, "liveStreamingDetails": {"actualEndTime": "2026-03-13T23:55:40Z", "actualStartTime": "2026-03-13T22:01:16Z", "scheduledStartTime": "2026-03-13T22:01:02Z"}}', '2026-03-29 09:20:18', '2026-03-29 09:33:16'),
	(70, 3, 'aPGa_a0BVis', 'Where Do We See the Mass in Acts of the Apostles? Bible Questions w/Tom Nash', 'where-do-we-see-the-mass-in-acts-of-the-apostles-bible-questions-wtom-nash', 'Donate: https://www.catholicanswersradio.com\n\nMore Catholic Answers: https://www.catholic.com\nBook a speaker: https://www.catholic.com/speakers\n\nSUBSCRIBE TO CA LIVE CLUB:  \nhttps://wvw.catholic.com/radioclub?email\n\nTopic: Bible Questions\nGuest: Tom Nash\n\n0:00 Intro\n01:20 - Where do we see the Mass in Acts of the Apostles?  \n09:38 - How do we defend the baptism of infants? My co-worker says you just need faith and it’s not necessary to baptize babies.  \n17:52 - In Mark 12:30ff Jesus quotes the great shema. In Deuteronomy it says to love God with your whole heart, soul, and strength. Why does Mark add the word “mind” to that?  \n22:15 - Why do some people feel reluctant to go to confession?  \n28:39 - Is the papacy so tied to Rome that it could never be somewhere else? If Islam took over Europe could the pope be based somewhere else?  \n31:58 - Why isn’t the book of Maccabees in the King James Bible? I’m trying to talk about the faith with my Seventh Day Adventist family members.  \n41:00 - Mt 10:3 calls James son of Alpheus, and Mk 2:14-17 calls Levi the son of Alpheus. Could they be brothers?  \n44:17 - My grown children think we are living in a simulation. How can I counter this?  \n50:13 - You said the King James did not translate the deuterocan books. But I have two KJV Bibles that include the deuterocanonical books.  \n52:01 - I’ve been getting along with my new coworkers because they are Christian. But today Mary came up and they really attacked Catholic teaching on Mary. What can I say to them?  \n\nFor more, visit catholic.com', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aPGa_a0BVis/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-03-13 11:03:57', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aPGa_a0BVis', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/aPGa_a0BVis', 'PT55M7S', 1513, 0, 21, '{"id": "aPGa_a0BVis", "etag": "hvqRAcoZqcQM6