	(83, 7, 'VMq0cGOY2JQ', 'Social Media in Light & Darkness', 'social-media-in-light-darkness', 'Friends, in this week\'s episode of the Word on Fire Show, Fr. Steve Grunow and I join Dr. Tod Worner to discuss the shadow side of social media and what faithful Catholics are called to do about it. \n\nWe also reflect on the prayer, study, and humility required to evangelize effectively online. \n\n\n00:00 | Introduction\n00:49 | Examining social media’s shadow side\n14:32 | Can teachers of the faith use social media without oversight?\n22:18 | How we prepare for online ministry\n27:58 | Join the Word on Fire Institute', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VMq0cGOY2JQ/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-03-16 13:00:54', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VMq0cGOY2JQ', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/VMq0cGOY2JQ', 'PT28M32S', 23712, 0, 10, '{"id": "VMq0cGOY2JQ", "etag": "uAE04rRfDZUm1mWHNFEYlBKC-6I", "kind": "youtube#video", "snippet": {"title": "Social Media in Light & Darkness", "channelId": "UCcMjLgeWNwqL2LBGS-iPb1A", "localized": {"title": "Social Media in Light & Darkness", "description": "Friends, in this week\'s episode of the Word on Fire Show, Fr. Steve Grunow and I join Dr. Tod Worner to discuss the shadow side of social media and what faithful Catholics are called to do about it. \\n\\nWe also reflect on the prayer, study, and humility required to evangelize effectively online. \\n\\n\\n00:00 | Introduction\\n00:49 | Examining social media’s shadow side\\n14:32 | Can teachers of the faith use social media without oversight?\\n22:18 | How we prepare for online ministry\\n27:58 | Join the Word on Fire Institute"}, "categoryId": "19", "thumbnails": {"high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VMq0cGOY2JQ/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VMq0cGOY2JQ/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VMq0cGOY2JQ/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VMq0cGOY2JQ/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VMq0cGOY2JQ/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}}, "description": "Friends, in this week\'s episode of the Word on Fire Show, Fr. Steve Grunow and I join Dr. Tod Worner to discuss the shadow side of social media and what faithful Catholics are called to do about it. \\n\\nWe also reflect on the prayer, study, and humility required to evangelize effectively online. \\n\\n\\n00:00 | Introduction\\n00:49 | Examining social media’s shadow side\\n14:32 | Can teachers of the faith use social media without oversight?\\n22:18 | How we prepare for online ministry\\n27:58 | Join the Word on Fire Institute", "publishedAt": "2026-03-16T14:00:54Z", "channelTitle": "Bishop Robert Barron", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "891", "viewCount": "23712", "commentCount": "118", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "false", "duration": "PT28M32S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "licensedContent": false}}', '2026-03-29 09:21:35', '2026-03-29 09:33:17'),
	(84, 7, '7y3_me_hEBU', 'The Light of the World - Bishop Barron\'s Sunday Sermon', 'the-light-of-the-world-bishop-barrons-sunday-sermon', 'Friends, on this Fourth Sunday of Lent, we hear the incomparably rich story of the man born blind, which has beguiled Christians up and down the centuries. We are meant to identify with this man: All of us are born into a world that has been infected by cruelty and violence and hatred. Original sin blinds us; it takes us out of the light. But Christ declares himself “the light of the world”—the one who will heal and illumine the eyes of us all.\n\nMass Readings: \nReading 1 — 1 Samuel 16:1b, 6-7, 10-13a\nPsalm — Psalm 23: 1-3a, 3b-4, 5, 6\nReading 2 — Ephesians 5:8-14\nGospel — John 9:1-41\n\n———VIDEO LINKS———\n\nThe Stations of the Cross with Bishop Barron: https://youtu.be/pJNjtA-Awb4\nThe Sorrowful Mysteries: https://youtu.be/ry7FbjkN-p0\nLiturgy of the Hours: Night Prayer for Sunday: https://youtu.be/8MNMUXB8XuQ\n\n———WATCH———\n\nSubscribe to this Channel: https://bit.ly/31LV1sn\nWord on Fire Institute Channel: https://www.youtube.com/@word-on-fire\nWord on Fire en Español Channel: https://www.youtube.com/@WOF-ES\n\n———WORD ON FIRE———\n\nWord on Fire: https://www.wordonfire.org/\nWord on Fire Español: https://www.wordonfire.org/es/\nFREE Daily Gospel Reflections (English or Español): https://dailycatholicgospel.com/\n\n———WORD ON FIRE INSTITUTE———\n\nJoin Bishop Barron and over 20,000 evangelists inside the Word on Fire Institute at https://wordonfire.institute\n\n———SOCIAL MEDIA———\n\nBishop Barron Instagram: https://bit.ly/2Sn2XgD\nBishop Barron Facebook: https://bit.ly/2Sltef5\nBishop Barron Twitter: https://bit.ly/2Hkz6yQ\n\nWord on Fire Instagram: https://bit.ly/39sGNyZ\nWord on Fire Facebook: https://bit.ly/2HmpPpW\nWord on Fire Twitter: https://bit.ly/2UKO49h\n\nWord on Fire en Español Instagram: https://bit.ly/38mqofD\nWord on Fire en Español Facebook: https://bit.ly/2SlthaL\nWord on Fire en Español Twitter: https://b