-E4/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rlB1JBwt-E4/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rlB1JBwt-E4/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rlB1JBwt-E4/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}}, "description": "Friends, Fr. Steve Grunow, Dr. Tod Worner, and I discuss the relationship between Catholic ministry and social media in this week’s episode of the Word on Fire Show.\\n\\n00:00 | ﻿Introduction\\n﻿﻿00:51 | ﻿What is social media?﻿\\n﻿﻿02:51 | ﻿Word on Fire and the early days of YouTube﻿\\n﻿﻿06:40 | ﻿Acting in faith, trusting in providence﻿\\n﻿﻿09:55 | ﻿Why a special commitment to new media?\\n16:08 | Examining the ministry’s evangelical reach﻿\\n21:50 | ﻿Join the Word on Fire Institute", "publishedAt": "2026-03-02T15:00:07Z", "channelTitle": "Bishop Robert Barron", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "702", "viewCount": "19991", "commentCount": "47", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "false", "duration": "PT22M20S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "licensedContent": false}, "liveStreamingDetails": {"actualEndTime": "2026-03-02T15:24:27Z", "actualStartTime": "2026-03-02T15:00:07Z", "scheduledStartTime": "2026-03-02T15:00:00Z"}}', '2026-03-29 09:21:35', '2026-03-29 09:33:17'),
	(91, 7, 'YSqp-I1Lnbk', 'The Adventure of Salvation - Bishop Barron\'s Sunday Sermon', 'the-adventure-of-salvation-bishop-barrons-sunday-sermon', 'Friends, on this Second Sunday of Lent, our first reading about Abraham and Matthew’s account of the Transfiguration orient us to a basic biblical principle. God has made us to go out from ourselves, to experience the splendor of reality. The more we let go of ourselves and our prerogatives—and the less we try to grasp and hang on to things—the more alive we become. Salvation, therefore, has a lot to do with adventure.\n\nMass Readings: \nReading 1 — Genesis 12:1-4a\nPsalm — Psalm 33:4-5, 18-19, 20, 22\nReading 2 —2 Timothy 1:8-10\nGospel — Matthew 17:1-9\n\n———VIDEO LINKS———\n\n\nThe Real Presence of Jesus in the Eucharist: https://youtu.be/UzCPu_lEhe8\nThe Sorrowful Mysteries: https://youtu.be/ry7FbjkN-p0\nLiturgy of the Hours: Night Prayer for Sunday: https://youtu.be/8MNMUXB8XuQ\n\n———WATCH———\n\nSubscribe to this Channel: https://bit.ly/31LV1sn\nWord on Fire Institute Channel: https://www.youtube.com/@word-on-fire\nWord on Fire en Español Channel: https://www.youtube.com/@WOF-ES\n\n———WORD ON FIRE———\n\nWord on Fire: https://www.wordonfire.org/\nWord on Fire Español: https://www.wordonfire.org/es/\nFREE Daily Gospel Reflections (English or Español): https://dailycatholicgospel.com/\n\n———WORD ON FIRE INSTITUTE———\n\nJoin Bishop Barron and over 20,000 evangelists inside the Word on Fire Institute at https://wordonfire.institute\n\n———SOCIAL MEDIA———\n\nBishop Barron Instagram: https://bit.ly/2Sn2XgD\nBishop Barron Facebook: https://bit.ly/2Sltef5\nBishop Barron Twitter: https://bit.ly/2Hkz6yQ\n\nWord on Fire Instagram: https://bit.ly/39sGNyZ\nWord on Fire Facebook: https://bit.ly/2HmpPpW\nWord on Fire Twitter: https://bit.ly/2UKO49h\n\nWord on Fire en Español Instagram: https://bit.ly/38mqofD\nWord on Fire en Español Facebook: https://bit.ly/2SlthaL\nWord on Fire en Español Twitter: https://bit.ly/38n3VPt\n\n———SUPPOR