	(134, 6, 'w59k1FcNpc8', 'Catholics, Pentecostals, and the Reality of Spiritual Warfare - On the Journey short', 'catholics-pentecostals-and-the-reality-of-spiritual-warfare-on-the-journey-short', 'Jesus, in his public ministry, frequently cast out demons as a sign that the Kingdom of God had truly come. He gave His apostles the authority to do the same, and throughout the pages of the New Testament, the sobering existence of demonic influence and the mighty reality of angelic power are well documented.\n\nFormer Pentecostal pastor Kenny Burchard shares how, while some Christian traditions de-emphasize or even dismiss the role of angels and demons in the world, Catholics and Pentecostals share a robust common ground when it comes to recognizing the reality of spiritual warfare.\n\nWatch the full episode: https://youtu.be/ws1U4V4GBwA?si=vRtTL3OYG_l2a14s\n\nThe Coming Home Network was established to help inquiring clergy and laity of various faiths -- or even no faith at all -- with fellowship, resources, and encouragement as they explore the possibility of becoming Catholic.\n\nFind out more about our work: https://www.chnetwork.org\n\nJoin our FREE Online Community: https://community.chnetwork.org\n\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/CHNetwork\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/chnetwork\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/cominghomenetwork\n\nSupport our mission: https://www.chnetwork.org/compass', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w59k1FcNpc8/maxresdefault.jpg', '2026-02-11 10:30:22', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w59k1FcNpc8', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/w59k1FcNpc8', 'PT3M54S', 516, 0, 13, '{"id": "w59k1FcNpc8", "etag": "UmBAt7bUvS-CsZTmzXPfkA4DL_o", "kind": "youtube#video", "snippet": {"tags": ["God", "Jesus", "Holy Spirit", "Prayer", "Becoming Catholic", "How to become Catholic", "Protestant to Catholic", "Pentecostal to Catholic", "Charismatic Catholic", "Foursquare to Catholic", "Catholicism vs Pentecostalism", "Pentecostal converts to Catholicism", "Charismatic Renewal", "Catholic Charismatic", "Renewal Ministries", "Ralph Martin", "Marcus Grodi", "EWTN", "The Journey Home", "Baptism in the Holy Spirit", "Charisms", "Spiritual Warfare", "Exorcism", "Exorcist", "Angels and Demons", "Demonic Influence", "Are Angels Real"], "title": "Catholics, Pentecostals, and the Reality of Spiritual Warfare - On the Journey short", "channelId": "UCIDebJFlV5aIsFs2jzxASrQ", "localized": {"title": "Catholics, Pentecostals, and the Reality of Spiritual Warfare - On the Journey short", "description": "Jesus, in his public ministry, frequently cast out demons as a sign that the Kingdom of God had truly come. He gave His apostles the authority to do the same, and throughout the pages of the New Testament, the sobering existence of demonic influence and the mighty reality of angelic power are well documented.\\n\\nFormer Pentecostal pastor Kenny Burchard shares how, while some Christian traditions de-emphasize or even dismiss the role of angels and demons in the world, Catholics and Pentecostals share a robust common ground when it comes to recognizing the reality of spiritual warfare.\\n\\nWatch the full episode: https://youtu.be/ws1U4V4GBwA?si=vRtTL3OYG_l2a14s\\n\\nThe Coming Home Network was established to help inquiring clergy and laity of various faiths -- or even no faith at all -- with fellowship, resources, and encouragement as they explore the possibility of becoming Catholic.\\n\\nFind out more about our work: https://www.chnetwork.org\\n\\nJoin our FREE Online Community: https://community.chnetwork.org\\n\\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/CHNetwork\\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/chnetwork\\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/cominghomenetwork\\n\\nSupport our mission: https://www.chnetwork.org/compass"}, "categoryId": "27", "thumbnails": {"high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w59k1FcNpc8/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w59k1FcNpc8/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w59k1FcNpc8/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w59k1FcNpc8/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w59k1FcNpc8/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}}, "description": "Jesus, in his public ministry, frequently cast out demons as a sign that the Kingdom of God had truly come. He gave His apostles the authority to do the same, and throughout the pages of the New Testament, the sobering existence of demonic influence and the mighty reality of angelic power are well documented.\\n\\nFormer Pentecostal pastor Kenny Burchard shares how, while some Christian traditions de-emphasize or even dismiss the role of angels and demons in the world, Catholics and Pentecostals share a robust common ground when it comes to recognizing the reality of spiritual warfare.\\n\\nWatch the full episode: https://youtu.be/ws1U4V4GBwA?si=vRtTL3OYG_l2a14s\\n\\nThe Coming Home Network was established to help inquiring clergy and laity of various faiths -- or even no faith at all -- with fellowship, resources, and encouragement as they explore the possibility of becoming Catholic.\\n\\nFind out more about our work: https://www.chnetwork.org\\n\\nJoin our FREE Online Community: https://community.chnetwork.org\\n\\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/CHNetwork\\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/chnetwork\\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/cominghomenetwork\\n\\nSupport our mission: https://www.chnetwork.org/compass", "publishedAt": "2026-02-11T11:30:22Z", "channelTitle": "The Coming Home Network International", "defaultLanguage": "en", "defaultAudioLanguage": "en-US", "liveBroadcastContent": "none"}, "statistics": {"likeCount": "33", "viewCount": "516", "commentCount": "1", "favoriteCount": "0"}, "contentDetails": {"caption": "false", "duration": "PT3M54S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "projection": "rectangular", "contentRating": [], "